NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, substantial battery.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for thirty-six (36) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
2) Maintain fulltime employment/schooling/work search or combination;
3) Spend eight (8) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, commencing on 02-16-16 by 8:00 a.m.;
4) Pay court costs;
5) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
6) provide DNA sample;
7) AODA assessment and follow through;
8) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same.
The Court denies the defendant's request for expungement.
$400.00 cash bail to be applied to court costs.
If revoked, the defendant has credit for 17 days.  (05-10-15 to 05-27-15)
Letter from Serenity Rehabiliation.
Minutes.
